Sentencas: Chromia scale growth and Cr evaporation of ferritic stainless steel interconnects are known to be major causes of serious degradation of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stack.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: The development of suitable ceramic coating materials on the metallic interconnects has been demonstrated as an effective way to address these challenges.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Herein, we developed a Mn1.35CO1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 (MCCY) spinel material via a facile glycine-nitrate process as a protective coating on a metallic interconnect (SUS 441).
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Crystal structure and surface charge state analysis of the MCCY material revealed that co-doping of Y and Cu into the (Mn,Co)(3)O-4 spinel resulted in redistribution of the Mn ions (Mn3+ and Mn4+) into the octahedral site, which increased the electrical conduction by enhanced small polaron hopping.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Accordingly, the MCCuY-coated interconnect exhibited similar to 8 times lower area specific resistance (ASR) than that of the undoped Mn1.5Co1.5O4 (MCO) coated interconnect.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Moreover, time-dependent ASR behavior of MCCuY-coated sample was monitored in-situ using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy at 650 degrees C, showing excellent stability with no observable change for >1000 h, while the ASR of the MCO-coated sample was raised by similar to 71%.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: After 1000 h operation, we found strong adhesion between the MCCuY coating and the metallic interconnect as well as remarkably restricted Cr diffusion into the coating layer.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Furthermore, the parabolic constant associated with the oxidation kinetics of the MCCuY-coated substrate (8.25 x 10(-11) mg(2) cm(-4) s(-1)) was similar to 1 order of magnitude lower than that of the MCO-coated one (7.34 x 10(-10) mg(2) cm(-4)
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: s(-1)) at 650 degrees C after 1000 h measurement.
Titulo: Highly conductive and stable Mn1.35Co1.35Cu0.2Y0.1O4 spinel protective coating on commercial ferritic stainless steels for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that the MCCuY is a highly promising coating material of metallic interconnects for intermediate-temperature SOFC applications.
